==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: phoneme
<hw>pho"neme</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"n⟦esl⟧m)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>One of a small set of speech sounds that
are used by and distinguished by the speakers of a particular language.
They are combined into <partof>morphemes</partof>,
<partof>words</partof>, and <partof>sentences</partof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>phonemic</ent>⟦br⟧
